<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 HERE'S THE STORY: Critics said it wouldn't last, but the phenomenon that is 
television's "Brady Bunch" turns 25 today. Ever wonder where the Bradys lived? 
It was never revealed on the show, but the suburban home seen in countless 
reruns still stands in North Hollywood (B1). . . . Not everyone is celebrating 
the anniversary. "I'm not a believer in milestones," said series creator 
Sherwood Schwartz. 
</P>
<P>
 DRIVING COSTS: So how much does it set you back to get to and from work? 
According to the nonprofit Commuter Transportation Services, the average 
commuter spends $86 to get to work each month. . . . The most expensive form of 
commuting is riding the train, at $97 monthly. Second is driving alone, at $92. 
Car-pooling is $68, and riding the bus $52. The cheapest is van-pooling, which 
averages $51. 
</P>
<P>
 OLDER RASCAL: His real name is Ernest Weckbaugh. Who? Well, maybe it would be 
better to just call him Stinky. That's who Burbank's Weckbaugh (above), played 
more than 50 years ago in the "Our Gang" comedies featuring the original Little 
Rascals (B5). . . . "I was one of hundreds of kids chosen to interact with the 
main characters," he says. 
</P>
<P>
 ON TRIAL: Two years ago, John Hoglund became the first Maywood police officer 
killed in the line of duty. This week, three men go on trial for the slaying, 
which authorities believe was part of a robbery spree that also killed Lee Chul 
Kim, a Van Nuys market owner, in May, 1992. . . . Authorities say Kim was shot 
about a dozen times, allegedly by two of the same suspects in the Hoglund case 
(B1). 
</P>
<P>
 WHICH CAMPUS? The starting premise is easy enough: Students who live within a 
mile of a school should attend that campus because they can walk to it. But 
what to do in Santa Clarita, where five of the six elementary schools are 
within a mile of each other? . . . Plus, a seventh school, outside the city 
limits, is due to open next fall, and some students will have to be moved, 
which has some parents unhappy (B6). 
</P>
</TEXT>
