<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: HOLIDAY WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gandhi's Birthday: On Sunday, Oct. 2, Indians observe Gandhi Jayanti, the 
125th anniversary of Mohandas K. Gandhi's birth.His doctrine of nonviolent 
resistance helped win Indian independence from the British Empire shortly after 
World War II. Born in 1869 in Porbandar, India, Gandhi was assassinated in New 
Delhi Jan. 30, 1948. 
</P>
<P>
 To commemorate his birth, readings from the world's major religious texts, 
including the Bible, the Bhagavad Gita and the Koran, are held at the Jumna 
River, where his body was cremated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
