<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UC IRVINE STUNS UCLA IN SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine pulled off the biggest victory in the history of its men's soccer 
program with a 4-3 upset of second-ranked UCLA in a Mountain Pacific Sports 
Federation game Sunday at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fifth consecutive victory for the Anteaters (6-1), who are off to 
their best start.UCLA, the conference favorite, is 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine took a 3-0 lead at the half before UCLA rallied with two goals early 
in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine's Pat Stark scored from seven yards with about nine minutes left to 
put the Anteaters ahead, 4-2. John Houston had the assist. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA's Justin Selander scored with about four minutes left for the Bruins, but 
UC Irvine hung on. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Succi, Manny Hernandez and Rich Breza scored in the first half for UC 
Irvine. Chris Taylor had 10 saves for the Anteaters. 
</P>
<P>
 P.J. Polowski had two assists for UC Irvine and leads the team with 18 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Mountain Pacific Sports Federation game: 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno State 3, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Visiting Cal State Fullerton (5-2-1, 
0-1) was called for three yellow cards in an intense game between two top-20 
teams. The Titans, ranked 17th, were called for 23 fouls and Fresno was 
assessed for 24. 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno, ranked 10th, is 7-1, 1-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 USC 9, UC Irvine 4 -- UC Irvine led, 2-0, but second-ranked USC scored eight 
consecutive goals at Heritage Park in Irvine. Omar Amr had two goals and Matt 
Maunz and Peter Muller scored the other goals for UC Irvine (2-5), which is 
ranked seventh in the nation. 
</P>
