SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Airline Slots at John Wayne: The Orange County Airport Commission will 
consider on Wednesday whether to recommend a proposal that would allow new 
airlines to start service at John Wayne Airport by affiliating with carriers 
that already operate there. The proposal was prompted by Reno Air, which wanted 
to acquire landing slots under an agreement with American Airlines that would 
have allowed it to begin offering service between Orange County and San 
Jose.That arrangement drew protests from other carriers and intervention by 
federal authorities. Officials at John Wayne, which limits flights to meet 
strict noise regulations, say they hope the new plan will allow low-fare 
carriers to offer service that would give passengers more options. The 
commission will meet at 7 p.m. in the Thomas F. Riley Terminal building at the 
airport. 
</P>
