SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: THE SOUTHLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New Home Sales Report: Builders across Southern California will be paying 
close attention to Thursday's Commerce Department report on August new-home 
sales.Rising mortgage rates hurt sales throughout most of the summer, and 
developers are hoping for a late burst of activity before the traditional fall 
and winter doldrums set in. However, not all builders are optimistic that sales 
will rebound, and many are already canceling or delaying new projects. Last 
week, the Commerce Department said the number of housing projects started in 
August tumbled 14% in the West, where California accounts for about half of all 
construction activity. 
