AT LEAST 16 KILLED BY FLASH FLOOD IN THAILAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A flash flood swept through a park Sunday, killing at least 16 people.Six 
people were injured and 17 others were missing. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Lance Cpl. Uthai Kietipong said the victims were swimming in a stream 
in Wang Takrai park, a popular recreation area at the foot of a mountain 50 
miles northeast of Bangkok. 
</P>
<P>
 A witness said park officials sounded a warning buzzer only moments before the 
water rushed into the park. 
