<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; CITY TO HOLD FREE EXPO ON SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the first time in its five-year history, the community expo will be held 
outdoors and remain open after dusk. The event is Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Laguna Niguel Chamber of Commerce, the expo's primary sponsor, expects 
about 25,000 people to attend the free event on El Lazo Road. 
</P>
<P>
 It is set to run from 10:30 a.m. to 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The evening portion of the event will feature a musical tribute to the 
Temptations and the Four Tops. 
</P>
<P>
 The expo will also offer an international food feast presented by 30 local 
restaurants, a "fun zone" with games, clowns and face painting for children, 
and more than 175 business exhibition booths. 
</P>
<P>
 It will take place on El Lazo between the Design Center South and the Chet 
Holifield Federal Building, also known as the Ziggurat. LYNN FRANEY 
