<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ANAHEIM; EMERGENCY RESPONSE SESSION IS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Officials will offer an orientation for emergency response volunteers Oct. 8 
from 8:30 to 11:30 a.m. at the North Net Fire Training Center, 2400 E. 
Orangewood Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The orientation is designed to prepare volunteers to help during a major 
disaster in tasks that would include damage and casualty assessment, emergency 
communications and shelter assistance. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are always looking for more people we can train to assist us during a 
major disaster," said Anaheim Fire Chief Jeff Bowman. "This orientation is the 
first step in mobilizing our citizen volunteers and allows them to give back to 
the community before and during a disaster." 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Anaheim Fire Department at (714) 254-4000. 
MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
