<P>
PEOPLE: EMULEX CORP. APPOINTS 3 NEW VICE PRESIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Peitler has been promoted to senior vice president of worldwide sales for 
Emulex Corp., a Costa Mesa computer products manufacturer.He joined the company 
last year with more than 25 years of experience in technical sales and 
marketing. In addition, Teri Blackledge and Chuck Goff were appointed vice 
presidents. Blackledge, who joined Emulex in 1991 as a marketing manager, was 
previously senior director of marketing. Goff, who is based at the 
manufacturing plant in Puerto Rico, was senior director of manufacturing prior 
to his promotion. 
</P>
