<TEXT>
<P>
 Backing Sought to Lease Airports: In a major turnaround, the government will 
seek endorsement at a party conference this week to lease all of its 22 
airports rather than sell them.The federal Cabinet last week approved a plan to 
lease all the airports currently owned and operated by the Federal Airports 
Corp. -- everything from Melbourne's Tullamarine Airport and Sydney's Mascot 
Airport to smaller regional sites. However, the proposal must be ratified by 
delegates to the Labor Party's national conference this week in Hobart. In May, 
the government announced it would to put the airports on the block as part of 
its asset sales program. But since then, criticism has intensified within Labor 
Party ranks over the proposal. 
</P>
