<TEXT>
<P>
 Unemployment Crisis Looms: China admitted the problem last week, and that 268 
million new job seekers -- more than the population of most countries -- are 
expected to join the hunt by 1999. The Labor Ministry has set a two-year 
program to expand the domestic labor market to try to keep the official 
unemployment rate below 3%, the China Daily newspaper said. By the turn of the 
century, China expects to see 200 million more rural job seekers and 68 million 
more in the cities, the newspaper quoted Zhang Xiaojian, director of the 
department of labor and employment, as saying. 
</P>
