</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jobless Figures Rise: Unemployment in the Philippines rose to 9.71% of the 
work force in July, the government said, as the expanding economy failed to 
create enough jobs to keep pace with population increases.A year ago, the 
unemployment rate was 8.58%. The estimated labor population rose by more than 1 
million from 41.152 million in July, 1993, to 42.366 million. The labor force, 
or the number of people of working age looking for jobs, rose 2% to 27.340 
million. Gross domestic product grew 5.1% in the first half of 1994, more than 
double the 2.3% rate a year before, the National Statistics Office said. 
</P>
