<P>
 Car Purchases to Be Subsidized: The government, keen to build a world-class 
auto industry, said last week that it would subsidize private car buyers and 
"support" four major plants that make Volkswagens, Peugeots and Daihatsus. The 
new industrial policy, unveiled in Beijing by Minister of Machinery He 
Guangyuan, buries the socialist-era doctrine that until recent years restricted 
