<P>
MAN, 82, KILLED CROSSING BOULEVARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 82-year-old man was killed as he crossed Ventura Boulevard mid-block and 
was struck by an oncoming truck, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, identified as Richard Allen of Tarzana, died instantly Saturday 
night of massive, multiple injuries, a spokesman for the Los Angeles County 
coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
 Allen apparently stepped into the street between parked cars and was not seen 
in time by Dennis Reese, 18, of Encino, who was driving a 1988 Nissan 
Pathfinder, said Los Angeles Police Officer Robert Kalstrom. 
</P>
<P>
 Reese was not charged, although an investigation into the accident is 
continuing, Kalstrom said. 
