<P>
1 DEAD, 1 WOUNDED IN CERRITOS SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies were searching Sunday for whoever shot 
and killed one man and left a second man to perish in a burning truck in 
Cerritos. 
</P>
<P>
 The second man, identified as Edward Burton Whitaker, 35, of Norwalk, was shot 
in the head and upper body but survived the attack, said sheriff's spokeswoman 
Deputy Benita Hinojos. 
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters had been called to Norwalk Boulevard and 166th Street at about 
2:30 a.m. by a report of a pickup truck on fire, Hinojos said. 
</P>
<P>
 They found a man identified as Gene Kennedy, 35, of Norwalk, dead in the bed 
of the truck. Whitaker, in spite of his wounds, was found walking nearby. 
</P>
<P>
 Whitaker was taken to a local hospital, where he was in critical condition 
Sunday. Deputies declined to release the name of the hospital for security 
reasons. 
</P>
