</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Donna Velin, deputy city clerk for the past three years, will be considered 
for appointment as city clerk at tonight's City Council meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager Robert C. Dunek is recommending that Velin officially assume the 
duties of the city clerk while remaining as his secretary. 
</P>
<P>
 If the council approves the recommendation, Velin, who also has served as 
Dunek's secretary since 1991, will receive a 4% pay raise, boosting her salary 
from $3,389 to $3,525 monthly. 
</P>
<P>
 Dunek has served as both city manager and city clerk since 1989. Now, he said, 
"it would be more efficient for the city to split the responsibilities." 
</P>
<P>
 As the city's official record-keeper, the city clerk keeps records and keeps 
the minutes of council meetings and is responsible for state-required filings, 
such as conflict-of-interest and election-related statements. 
</P>
<P>
 Dunek said that Velin has attended several seminars on the duties of city 
clerks and has gained experience with routine duties and responsibilities. 
</P>
<P>
 "She is very capable of assuming the duties of the city clerk at this time," 
Dunek said in a report to the council. BERT ELJERA 
