YORBA LINDA MAN KILLED IN CAR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 30-year-old Yorba Linda man was killed Saturday night when he apparently 
drove through a red light at a busy intersection and was hit by another car. 
The collision sent the victim's car careening into a signpost, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, whose name was not released pending notification of his family, 
was driving alone in a 1985 blue Dodge Colt westbound on Orangethorpe Avenue 
about 9 p.m. when he entered the intersection at Lakeview Avenue against the 
red light and was hit by a 1991 Honda driven by Trudy Elaine Wilson, 44, of 
Yorba Linda, police said. The man's vehicle then hit a speed limit sign, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man suffered massive head and internal injuries and was taken to UCI 
Medical Center in Orange, where he was pronounced dead at 9:52 p.m., police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither Wilson nor her passengers were injured, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 No citations or arrests have been made and an investigation of the incident is 
underway, police said. Anyone who witnessed the traffic accident is being asked 
to call Investigator Chuck O'Connor at (714) 254-1835. 
</P>
